  "text": "Let K ω , ω ∈ Ω, be a measurable family of compact subsets of T d satisfying (1.10) with f (ω) the same as in the Introduction. Set K = {(x, ω) : x ∈ K ω }. Then we have the setup of \"random bundle maps\" from [CITATION_1] , and can speak about the relativized topological entropy h (r) top (τ, K) of the skew product transformation τ restricted to the τ -invariant set K.",
